objectives.name: Primary Technology Development Objective
objectives.text: To help design and validate a novel technology to remotely provide exercise intervention for people at risk or with some level of dementia

objectives.name: Remote Assessment Objective
objectives.text: To enable remote assessment of cognitive-motor performance via wearable sensors through playing a simple interactive game named iTMT

objectives.name: Cognitive Function Preservation Objective
objectives.text: To preserve cognitive function in people with MCI through remote exercise intervention

objectives.name: Balance and Mobility Improvement Objective
objectives.text: To improve balance and cognition during distractive conditioning while the exercise is remotely supervised by a telemedicine interface

objectives.name: Fear of Falling Reduction Objective
objectives.text: To reduce fear of falling in older adults with mild cognitive impairment

objectives.name: Independent Living Promotion Objective
objectives.text: To promote independent living and reduce costs associated with consequence of cognitive-motor decline including falls and frailty

objectives.name: Sex Difference Exploratory Objective
objectives.text: To examine whether the benefit of exercise is dependent on sex (sex as biological factor)

objectives.name: Confounder Correlation Exploratory Objective
objectives.text: To determine whether the magnitude of gain is correlated with confounders including age, baseline cognitive performance, baseline motor performance, and BMI

endpoints.name: Center of Mass Sway
endpoints.text: Change in center of mass (COM) sway area in medial-lateral direction during eyes-open stance at 6 weeks compared to baseline

endpoints.name: Remote Exercise Feasibility
endpoints.text: Feasibility of remotely-supervised exercise platform measured by completion rate of exercise sessions

endpoints.name: Technology Acceptability
endpoints.text: Acceptability of the teleexergame platform measured by acceptability questionnaire at follow up visit

endpoints.name: iTMT Cognitive Performance
endpoints.text: Cognitive-motor performance assessed via iTMT (interactive Trail Making Test) using wearable sensors

endpoints.name: Remote Motor Assessment
endpoints.text: Motor performance parameters captured remotely via wearable sensor system

endpoints.name: Trail Making Test A
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in Trail-Making Test A (TMT-A) score post exercise

endpoints.name: MoCA Score
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA) score

endpoints.name: Balance Assessment
endpoints.text: Balance quantified using BalanSens measuring ankle and hip motion in 3D, 2D COM sway, and RCI in ML and AP directions during Romberg protocol

endpoints.name: Gait Parameters
endpoints.text: Spatio-temporal gait parameters including velocity, stride length, stride time, double support, single support, stride-to-stride variability, and gait initiation assessed using LegSys

endpoints.name: Timed Up and Go
endpoints.text: Timed-up-and-go (TUG) test performance

endpoints.name: Fear of Falling
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in Falls Efficacy Scale-International (FES-I) score

endpoints.name: Daily Physical Activity
endpoints.text: Physical activity parameters including number of steps, duration of sitting, standing, walking and lying, postural transitions measured by PAMSys over 48 hours

endpoints.name: Quality of Life
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in quality of life measured by PROMIS Global scale

endpoints.name: Sex-Based Balance Improvement
endpoints.text: Comparison of gain in balance improvement between male and female participants

endpoints.name: Confounder Correlation Analysis
endpoints.text: Correlation of magnitude of gain with confounders including age, baseline cognitive performance, baseline motor performance, and BMI using Spearman correlation coefficient
